# 🧠 Machine Learning Guidance System Overview

The Machine Learning Guidance System functions as the intelligent decision-making layer of the proposed UAV-based industrial safety framework.

The subsystem is designed to analyze integrated sensing, telemetry, and environmental data in order to identify hazardous regions, estimate safer zones, and support intelligent evacuation guidance during industrial gas leakage scenarios.

The framework combines environmental sensing, spatial mapping, gas concentration analysis, and telemetry-based positional tracking to enable context-aware hazard evaluation and guidance generation.

---

# ⚙️ ML Guidance System Architecture

The machine learning framework follows a multi-layered analytical architecture consisting of:

- Data Acquisition Layer
- Sensor Fusion Layer
- Hazard Analysis Layer
- Spatial Mapping Layer
- Guidance Generation Layer

The architecture processes environmental and positional data streams to support intelligent monitoring and emergency response workflows.

---

# 🧩 Core Components

## Data Acquisition Module

The system continuously collects data from:

- MQ-series gas sensors
- LiDAR sensing framework
- Ultrasonic sensors
- Camera modules
- UAV telemetry logs
- GPS positional coordinates

The acquired data forms the primary input pipeline for environmental analysis and hazard evaluation.

---

## Sensor Fusion Layer

The sensor fusion framework integrates:

- Gas concentration readings
- Environmental sensing inputs
- UAV positional logs
- Spatial mapping data
- Telemetry information

This enables unified environmental representation and contextual hazard interpretation.

---

## Hazard Analysis System

The hazard analysis module performs:

- Gas concentration evaluation
- Hazard threshold classification
- Hazard zone identification
- Environmental condition analysis
- Risk estimation workflows

Environmental regions are categorized into:
- Safe Zones
- Moderate Risk Zones
- Hazardous Zones

based on integrated sensing data.

---

## Spatial Mapping Framework

The mapping layer associates gas concentration values with spatial coordinates to generate structured environmental representations.

The framework supports:
- Hazard localization
- Gas intensity distribution mapping
- Spatial hazard visualization
- Environmental modeling
- Safer region estimation

---

## Guidance Generation Module

The guidance framework analyzes processed environmental information to determine:

- Safer navigation regions
- Lower gas concentration areas
- Potential evacuation paths
- Directional guidance outputs

Guidance outputs may be delivered through:
- Visual indicators
- Monitoring dashboards
- Audio-based alerts
- Directional navigation cues

---

# 📡 Operational Workflow

The ML guidance system follows a structured analytical pipeline.

## Step 1 — Environmental Data Collection
Environmental sensing systems continuously acquire gas concentration and spatial data.

## Step 2 — Telemetry Integration
UAV telemetry logs and positional coordinates are integrated with sensing information.

## Step 3 — Sensor Fusion
Environmental and positional datasets are combined into a unified analytical framework.

## Step 4 — Hazard Classification
Gas concentration levels and environmental conditions are analyzed to identify hazardous regions.

## Step 5 — Spatial Analysis
The framework maps environmental hazards across spatial coordinates.

## Step 6 — Guidance Generation
The system estimates safer regions and generates evacuation guidance outputs.

